What will be the output of the following PHP code? 

$array = [10, 20, 30, 40, 50];
unset($array[2]);
$array = array_values($array);
echo $array[2];

What is the output of the following PHP code if the input string is 'Hello World'? 

$input = 'Hello World';
$output = substr_count($input, 'o');
echo $output;

What will be the output of the following PHP script if it is run as a standalone script? 

<?php
function test() {
    $x = 5;
    echo $x;
}
test();
echo $x;
?>

What will be the output of the following PHP code snippet?

<?php
function test() {
    $x = 5;
    echo $x;
}
test();
echo $x;
?>

What will the following PHP code output? 

&lt;?php 
    $x = 5; 
    function test() { 
        $x = 10; 
        echo $x; 
    } 
    test(); 
?&gt;

What will be the output of the following PHP code if no argument is passed to the function?

function makeCoffee($type = "Espresso") {
  return "Making a cup of $type";
}
echo makeCoffee();

What will be the output of the following PHP code snippet?

<?php
function test() {
  static $count = 0;
  $count++;
  echo $count;
}
test();
test();
test();
?>
